params._tokenId: ID of the token to approve.

params.amount: Amount of WSTON tokens to approve.

params._paymentMethod: Payment method to use for the purchase.
params._tokenId: ID of the GEM token to buy.

createPreminedGEM(uint8,uint8[2],uint8[4.details: the contract must hold enough WSTON to cover the entire supply of GEMs across all owners

returns._0: uint256 Returns the ID of the created GEM.

createPreminedGEMPool(uint8[],uint8[2][].details: the contract must hold enough WSTON to cover the entire supply of GEMs across all owners

params._colors: Array of color attributes for each GEM.
params._quadrants: Array of quadrant attributes for each GEM.
params._rarities: Array of rarities for each GEM.
params._tokenURIs: Array of URIs for each GEM token.

returns._0: uint256[] Returns an array of IDs for the created GEMs.

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleGranted} event.

params._gemFactory: Address of the gem factory contract.

returns._0: bytes4 Returns the selector of the onERC721Received function.

putGemForSale(uint256,uint256).details: we set approval for all for gas optimization (not approving for each gem one by one)

params._price: Price at which the GEM is to be sold.
params._tokenId: ID of the GEM token to put for sale.

putGemListForSale(uint256[],uint256[]).details: we set approval for all for gas optimization (not approving for each gem one by one)

params.prices: Array of prices at which each GEM is to be sold.
params.tokenIds: Array of GEM token IDs to put for sale.

params._tokenId: ID of the GEM token to remove from sale.

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `callerConfirmation`. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role. May emit a {RoleRevoked} event.

params._airdrop: New address of the airdrop contract.

params._gemFactory: New address of the gem factory contract.

params.marketplace: New address of the marketplace contract.

params._randomPack: New address of the random pack contract.

params._wstonSwapPool: New address of the WSTON swap pool.

transferTON(address,uint256).details: only the owner or the admins are authorized to call the function

params._amount: Amount of TON tokens to transfer.
params._to: Address to transfer TON tokens to.

returns._0: bool Returns true if the transfer is successful.

transferTreasuryGEMto(address,uint256).details: only the GemFactory, MarketPlace, RandomPack, Airdrop or the Owner are able to transfer Gems from the treasury

params._to: Address to transfer the GEM to.
params._tokenId: ID of the GEM token to transfer.

returns._0: bool Returns true if the transfer is successful.

transferWSTON(address,uint256).details: only the gemFactory, MarketPlace, RandomPack, Airdrop or the Owner are authorized to transfer the funds

params._amount: Amount of WSTON tokens to transfer.
params._to: Address to transfer WSTON tokens to.

returns._0: bool Returns true if the transfer is successful.

approveGem(address,uint256).notice: Approves a specific operator to manage a GEM token.

approveWstonForMarketplace(uint256).notice: Approves the marketplace to spend a specific amount of WSTON tokens.

buyGem(uint256,bool).notice: Buys a GEM from the marketplace.

createPreminedGEM(uint8,uint8[2],uint8[4.notice: Creates a premined GEM with specified attributes.

createPreminedGEMPool(uint8[],uint8[2][].notice: Creates a pool of premined GEMs with specified attributes.

initialize(address,address,address).notice: Initializes the Treasury contract with the given parameters.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.notice: Handles the receipt of an ERC721 token.

putGemForSale(uint256,uint256).notice: Puts a GEM for sale on the marketplace.

putGemListForSale(uint256[],uint256[]).notice: Puts a list of GEMs for sale on the marketplace.

removeGemFromSale(uint256).notice: Removes a GEM from sale on the marketplace.

setAirdrop(address).notice: Sets the address of the airdrop contract.

setGemFactory(address).notice: Sets the address of the gem factory.

setMarketPlace(address).notice: Sets the address of the marketplace contract.

setRandomPack(address).notice: Sets the address of the random pack contract.

setWstonSwapPool(address).notice: Sets the address of the WSTON swap pool.

tonApproveWstonSwapPool(uint256).notice: Approves the WSTON swap pool to spend TON tokens.

transferTON(address,uint256).notice: Transfers TON tokens to a specified address.

transferTreasuryGEMto(address,uint256).notice: Transfers a GEM from the treasury to a specified address.

transferWSTON(address,uint256).notice: Transfers WSTON tokens to a specified address.
